HEADWORD: Hereford
<hw>Her"e*ford</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a breed of
cattle originating in Herefordshire, England. The Herefords are good
working animals, and their beef-producing quality is
excellent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

